SIMPLE: protectorate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Protectorate
<hw>Pro*tect"or*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>protectorat</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Government by a
protector; -- applied especially to the government of England by Oliver
Cromwell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The authority assumed by a superior power over an
inferior or a dependent one, whereby the former protects the latter from
invasion and shares in the management of its affairs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protectorial</ent>⟦br⟧
